<br>
'The destruction of the gods and of humankind in a final battle between the Aesir and their enemies. {1760-1770}'<br>
<br>
School never taught me about the Aesir, and too many RPGs include stuff from it(Ragnarok, Odin, Thor) so I don't think it's real, but browsing around the internet some it seems like greek mythology and people call it an ancient civilization.  So it was real?  1760-1770 like the dictionary said doesn't sound too ancient, and too modern for people to believe it.  Also it mentions the gods interacting with 'middle-earth' which I thought was just the world in JR Tolkien stories?  Anyone that can help me out with some answers that knows a thing or two about this stuff?<br>
